Name: Burrower
Description: To dig a hole or tunnel for habitation or refuge. 2. To live or hide in such a place. 3. To move or progress by or as if by digging or tunneling:

Name: Climber
Description: a person or animal that climbs. a vine or climbing plant that readily grows up a support or over other plants.

Name: Clinger
Description: to adhere closely; stick to: The wet paper clings to the glass. 2. to hold tight, as by grasping or embracing; cleave

Name: Diver
Description: a person or animal that dives into water.

Name: Mixed
Description: consisting of different qualities or elements. containing a mixture of both favorable and negative elements. composed of different varieties of the same thing.

Name: Other
Description: used to refer to a person or thing that is different or distinct from one already mentioned or known about. further; additional.

Name: Skater
Description: a person who skates, especially on ice.

Name: Sprawler
Description: To sit or lie with the body and limbs spread out awkwardly. 2. To spread out in a straggling or disordered fashion: untidy tenements sprawling toward the river. v.tr. To cause to spread out in a straggling or disordered fashion.

Name: Swimmer
Description: a person or animal that swims. To move along in water, etc, by means of movements of the body or parts of the body.
